description: Compliance Energy Corporation engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral resource properties in Canada. The company primarily holds a 75% interest in the Raven Coal Deposit that covers approximately 3,100 hectares of coal rights; and a 100% interest in the Bear Coal Deposit, which consists of 8 coal licenses totaling 2,046 hectares in Vancouver Island. Compliance Energy Corporation was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. John A. Tapics B.Sc., P.Eng., B.Sc, P.Eng
